adjectives.description: unintriguing (comparative more unintriguing, superlative most unintriguing)

entries.meaning: Not involving oneself in secret plots or schemes.
examples: Impelled anew by what Byron calls 'The various joltings of life's hackney-coach,' he proceeded to Paris, and entered upon the office; but neither his age, nor his quiet unintriguing character, was congenial with the temper of such a scene; and he retired unsuccessful, but with the grant of a pension.
